@node "INFO" "SN Run v3.1 - Information"
@toc "MAIN"
┌───────────────────────────┐
  SN Run v3.1 - Information
└───────────────────────────┘

You've just got your hands on the BEST CNet RUN replacement ever!
Now you can run ARexx, C, DOS and Paragon PFiles, read text and run
DOS scripts using one command!

Uses ReqTools requesters if available!  (You need to have reqtools.library
and rexxreqtools.library in your libs:)

(I would have included the necessary files in this archive, but, as stated
in the rexxreqtools docs, the minimum distribution requires the docs to
rexxreqtools.  Huh, you ask?  I printed them out a long time ago and now I
can't find the originals on my drive.  If anyone has them, please mail
them to me!  :)

Features to note:
  - Multi-line compatible.  You don't have to worry about conflictions.
  - Self-cleaning.  Leaves no temp files lying around.
  - Uses ReqTools requesters, if available.

NOTE:  This is a compiled ARexx script.  However, it does not require any
       additional libraries or RPStart to function (unless otherwise
       noted in these docs).

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
