@node "INSTALL" "SN Run v3.1 - Installation Procedures"
@toc "MAIN"
┌───────────────────────────────────────┐
  SN Run v3.1 - Installation Procedures
└───────────────────────────────────────┘

 1  Run the included installation script either of the following
    two ways:

    a.  Type "Installer Install_Run" from the Shell.

    b.  Click on the "Install_Run" icon from Workbench.

 2  The installation script moves the required files to your specified
    location.

 3  Load up your bbstext and change CNet's internal RUN command from
    "RUN" to something like "CRN" so it's still usable.

    Add "RUN |{#1PFiles:SN_Run}" to your bbsmenu under "1; Maintenance,"
    below all the internal CNet commands.  Note that the above { is
    actually a control-Q command.

 4  Reload your bbstext/bbsmenu via CNet's Control Panel menu (option
    #3, "Text/menu reload  RAmiga-T" and you're all set!

 5  Run has three modes of operation:

    1.  RUN <no args>

        Brings up a menu of the filetype choices.  If ReqTools is available,
        a request will appear if no path/filename is given.

    2.  RUN type <no path/filename>

        type =  0 = ARexx
                1 = C
                2 = DOS
                3 = Paragon
                4 = DOS Script
                5 = View Textfile

        If ReqTools is available, immediately brings up a requester and runs
        the selected file using the given type.

    3.  RUN type path/filename

        Immediately runs the given file using the given type.

    If the specified drive/volumn doesn't exist or an assignment is not
    made, it will abort.  No requesters are ever popped up unless Run
    is damn sure someone is there to handle them.  :)

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@endnode
